      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PATH TO GREATNESS (2) is a smart pacer who has put two wins together at this circuit and distance, last time leading from one spot wider before going on to salute by 5.7m. That took his strike rate here to 50 per cent. The good draw gives him every chance to land the hat trick. BUDDY PERFECT (1) did a good job to continue a string of wins and placings by coming from the back row for a 3m second last week. Led from this barrier and fought well to score at this circuit and distance prior so is much better served by this draw. APPLIED NZ (5) deserved last week's win following consistent form. Draws wider but came from deeper still for two close seconds here last month. CHEZZ DALE NZ (12) may need luck from the second line but did well to overcome a wide barrier for a win here last start.",
